Steps:
[AUTH] POST {{BACK_URL}}/connect/token → save Bearer token
[SETUP] prepare JSON body: {"name": "API Test Promo {{timestamp}}", "isActive": true, "priority": 15, "storeId": "{{STORE_ID}}", "type": "Promotion"}
[HTTP] POST {{BACK_URL}}/api/marketing/promotions with Authorization header and JSON body

[AUTH] POST {{BACK_URL}}/connect/token → save Bearer token
[SETUP] GET /api/marketing/promotions to obtain an existing promotion id → save as {{promo_id}}
[SETUP] prepare PUT body with updated name: {"id": "{{promo_id}}", "name": "UPDATED {{timestamp}}", "isActive": true}
[HTTP] PUT {{BACK_URL}}/api/marketing/promotions/{{promo_id}} with Authorization and JSON body

[AUTH] POST {{BACK_URL}}/connect/token → save Bearer token
[SETUP] POST /api/marketing/promotions to create test promotion → save {{promo_id}}
[HTTP] DELETE {{BACK_URL}}/api/marketing/promotions?ids={{promo_id}} with Authorization header

[AUTH] obtain Bearer token for {{USER_EMAIL}} from storefront auth endpoint
[GQL] POST {{BACK_URL}}/graphql with query:
query {
  promotionCoupons(storeId: "{{STORE_ID}}", first: 20, after: "0") {
    totalCount
    items {
      id
      systemName
      name
      label
      description
      couponCode
      endDate
    }
  }
}

[GQL] POST {{BACK_URL}}/graphql with introspection query:
{
  __schema {
    queryType {
      fields {
        name
        args { name type { name kind ofType { name kind } } }
      }
    }
  }
}
[VAR] find 'promotionCoupons' field in queryType.fields

[AUTH] obtain Bearer token for {{USER_EMAIL}}
[GQL] POST {{BACK_URL}}/graphql with malformed query — omit storeId argument:
query {
  promotionCoupons(first: 10, after: "0") {
    totalCount
    items { id couponCode }
  }
}

[AUTH] obtain admin Bearer token
[SETUP] via REST API: ensure one promotion exists with isActive=false in {{STORE_ID}}
[SETUP] via REST API: ensure one promotion exists with isPublic=false (or 'private') in {{STORE_ID}}
[SETUP] via REST API: ensure one promotion with isActive=true AND isPublic=true AND at least 1 coupon exists
[GQL] POST {{BACK_URL}}/graphql: promotionCoupons(storeId: {{STORE_ID}}, first: 100, after: "0") with admin token

[AUTH] obtain Bearer token for {{USER_EMAIL}}
[GQL] POST /graphql: promotionCoupons(storeId: {{STORE_ID}}, cultureName: "en-US", first: 20, after: "0") { items { id name label description systemName } }
[VAR] save name/label/description values for en-US
[GQL] POST /graphql: promotionCoupons(storeId: {{STORE_ID}}, first: 20, after: "0") (no cultureName arg) { items { id name label description systemName } }

[GQL] POST {{BACK_URL}}/graphql with intentionally malformed promotionCoupons query (unknown field):
